2017 WW23 Purley-R Crystal Ridge Silver Release Announcement (\r\n BKC #10)

\r\n \r\n \r\n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\r\n \r\n
\r\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2017 WW23 Purley-R Crystal Ridge Silver release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\r\n \r\n Fedora25/\r\n \r\n WS2016\r\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

ES1 AEP DIMM Setup BKM 

\xc2\xb7        Update CR FW

If AEP DIMM is not healthy, we have two alternatives:

a.      Do AEP format

            1. Attach ITP to the SKX XDP port

            2. On the ElkValley pythonSV console, type below commands for DIMM formatting

            >>>itp.cv.resetbreak=1

            >>> sv.refresh()

            >>> fw.showBSR()

            >>>import falconvalley.fw.fnvFwFunctions as fw

            >>>fw.dfxFormat(unlockDimm=False)

            >>>itp.cv.resetbreak=0

            3. Power cycle the system

            4. Boot to UEFI shell and update CR

               ApachePassCli.efi load -f \xe2\x80\x93source  .\\< _strip.bin fw file> -dimm

b.     If step a is not working, use ITP/Jtag to update AEP FW and Syn SPD one by one, follow the BKM Setup_TAB_AEP_BKM_v1.1.docx

 

If AEP DIMM is health, use UEFI shell to update all AEP FW

               ApachePassCli.efi load \xe2\x80\x93f -source <path_to_strip.bin> - dimm

 \xc2\xb7     Goal/namespace can be created under UEFI or Linux

a.          UEFI: ApachePassCli.efi create -f -goal PersistentMemoryType=AppDirect

                 ApachePassCli.efi show -a \xe2\x80\x93pool

                 ApachePassCli.efi create \xe2\x80\x93namespace \xe2\x80\x93pool <pool_Id> Type=AppDirect

b.          Linux: ixpdimm-cli create \xe2\x80\x93f \xe2\x80\x93goal persistentmemorytype=appdirect

                   ixpdimm- cli show -a \xe2\x80\x93pool

                   ixpdimm-cli create \xe2\x80\x93namespace \xe2\x80\x93pool <pool_Id> Type=AppDirect

System\r\nScope Log

\r\n\r\n

\xc2\xb7       It is a log file that is\r\ngenerated by the SysScope tool from BKC systems. SysScope Tool and the user\r\nguide can be found in the BKC pkg, BKC consumers can use the SST tool on their\r\nown systems to generate an XML file describing their configuration. By\r\ncomparing XMLs, any differences between Intel\xe2\x80\x99s BKC system config and BKC\r\nconsumer systems can be quickly identified

\r\n\r\n

\xc2\xb7       \r\nFor\r\neasy readable, we capture the system\xe2\x80\x99s key info (CPU/PCH/BIOS/OS/AEP info) from\r\nBKC systems and put in html format -- here

Refer to the installation guide BKC package installation

Pedigree and Board Jumper Settings: 2S Guide

Note: Only mandatory and necessary optional rework is implemented by BKC team

\xc2\xb7      2s

o NC_RWK_I (Mandatory): Update BMC FW

o NC_RWK_K (Mandatory): Avoiding false LAN Wake Activations

o NC_RWK_L (Mandatory): Update CPLD FW

o NC_RWK_M (Mandatory): No-Boot without ITP issue fix

o Note: In case you have implemented Optional rework 20, you should move switch S4E2.4 to OFF position, otherwise the default position is ON.
